Fit Ridge regression

ridge.Rd

Fit Ridge regression

ridge(x, y, lambda = 10^seq(-10, 10, length.out = 100))

Arguments

x

matrix of examples
y

a vector, the response
lambda

regularization parameters

Value

a list, an object of class 'ridge'

Examples


n <- 100 ; p <- 10
X <- matrix(rnorm(n * p), n, p) # no intercept!
y <- rnorm(n)

(fit_obj <- ahead::ridge(X, y))
